</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uherbertdalovebug.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Herbert Dalovebug</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Secksie Troll Danzer</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/19/02 4:27:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2226.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The new guy...</span><hr size=1> They've cracked down on names, bigtime.  I see a person's name changed about twice a week now, as opposed to only ever seeing name changes 4 times in EverQuest in the past 2 years I've played.<br>
<br>
They even got me, for Herbert Dalovebug.  Two reasons, 1) &quot;Da&quot; is just not allowed. 2) I'd be the Disney Car.<br>
<br>
I think it was a couple of nights ago they nabbed a 45+ chanter named Soysauce on account of &quot;that 'item' wouldn't be available in the day and age that EverQuest takes place&quot;.  Last I checked, the year was 3000+.  Maybe I should wait until the year 8000 before I make my new character, Ketchup.  Will we have Ketchup in Norrath by then?<br>
<br>
Frankly, unless a name is obscene, fully detracting from the overall 'essence' of EverQuest, or otherwise disturbing, I see no reason the GMs should spend time harassing their client base if they're above level 40, or so.  Or if there was some way to gauge /played time and base it upon that, maybe that would be something.  After 40+ days on Herb, it hit me hard when they took my name away.  I'm not saying I'm entitled to keeping my name more than anyone else who is lev25 and only had 2 days played time.  I'm just saying that after 40+ days of played time in 8 months of EQ on Druzzil, I grew very attached to it.  And it stung when they took it away.<br>
<br>
Maybe Bogell's choosing to rule with an iron fist.  He doesn't bother to cover it up with a velvet glove, either.  Maybe all the little things he's doing that tick us off actually earn him brownie points with his boss.  He's gotta hold onto his job some way, I suppose.  So when I think about it, I can't blame him either.<br>
<br>
I just wish exceptions could be made, and I was one of them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I enjoy who I am in-game, and when I look at screenshots of myself shamelessly posing in F9 with friends, I do feel a lil sinking feeling in the pit of my stomach upon seeing no last name.  <br>
<br>
My only gripe is that he's addressing an issue that previous GMs let slide, and I happened to get caught in it.  It would have just been easier to have my name taken away from me 6 months ago as opposed to NOW.<br>
<br>
Maybe someday he'll run past the druid/ranger with the name &quot;Try Cunnilingus&quot; spelled backward.  Maybe someday he'll bump into (first name left blank intentionally) ______ Zarathustra, and say &quot;Heeey. Thats the equivalent of Christ, in another religion! Why the hell would someone name themselves &quot;Bob Christ&quot; in game?!?!&quot;.<br>
<br>
I didn't actually know Herbie Dalovebug was the Disney Car.  Hehe.  It was before my time, though I remember watching Herbie Goes Bananas.  Why are they called lovebugs, anyhow? I still don't get it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I just always played my name out to go in sync with the phrase &quot;bitten by a love bug&quot; and played a happy, goofy troll.<br>
<br>
I think Bogell's doin' his job. <br>
At the same time- I don't think he's focusing on good customer service, but just blindly adhering to the rules in the book.  I can't blame him...but at the same time..I am. <br>
<br>
I'll quit babbling now. Boy, I wish I didn't have that coffee this late at night.  Time to go watch the cartoon network.<br>
<br>
